# Qubic USA Ambassador Hackathon ‚Äî ‚ÄúRevolutions‚Äù

## Overview

The **Qubic USA Hackathon ‚Äî Revolutions** is the flagship developer initiative of the Qubic USA Ambassador Program. Its mission is to expand the **RPC-20 ecosystem**, accelerate real-world adoption, and onboard the next generation of **gaming developers, system engineers, and decentralized compute architects**.

At its core, Revolutions challenges builders to create the **Ultimate Qubic Wallet** ‚Äî a high-performance, Web3-native platform that merges gaming-grade UX, on-chain asset management, and Qubic‚Äôs distributed compute model into a single, production-ready system.

This wallet serves as the primary entry point for:

- Users  
- Miners  
- Traders  
- Game studios  

to interact with RPC-20 tokens, decentralized games, staking mechanisms, AI-powered smart contracts, and ecosystem analytics.

---

## Core Vision

Qubic offers several rare advantages in Web3:

### Feeless Microtransactions
Ideal for real-time gaming, wagers, in-game item transfers, and tournaments.

### On-Chain Randomness & Compute
Enables provably fair mechanics for poker, PvP, and arcade games.

### True Asset Ownership via RPC-20
Includes game tokens, skins, passes, IPO shares, and reward pools.

### Distributed AI & Smart Logic
Supports NPC behavior, matchmaking, fraud prevention, and dynamic economies.

The hackathon creates pathways for:

- Launching **Qubic-native games**  
- Integrating **paQman**, **snaQe**, and future arcade titles  
- Creating tokenized tournaments & esports economies  
- Monetizing through burns, IPO shares, and automated reward cycles  

---

# Hackathon Phases

## Phase 1 ‚Äî Preparation  
**December 2025 ‚Äì January 2026**

This phase focuses on:

- Securing **~30B QUBIC** in funding (via CCF + partners)  
- Finalizing **prize structures**  
- Building the **hackathon portal**, including:  
  - GitHub integrations  
  - RPC-20 documentation  
  - SDK access  
  - Developer learning materials  
- Preparing infrastructure:  
  - Testnet faucets  
  - Wallet setup guides  
  - Submission/review pipelines  

---

## Phase 2 ‚Äî Promotion & Onboarding  
**February 2026**

Goals:

- Attract **50‚Äì100 global builders**  
- Launch coordinated outreach via ambassadors, universities, gaming communities  
- Run a **3‚Äì4 week educational program**, including:  
  - Webinars  
  - AMAs  
  - Hands-on tutorials  
  - Mentor office hours  

---

## Phase 3 ‚Äî Execution & Building  
**March 2026 ‚Äî Hackathon Month**

Teams execute a **6-week sprint** with:

- Weekly milestone demos  
- Testnet faucets  
- GitHub commit verification  
- Live leaderboard tracking  

### Judging Criteria

| Category | Weight |
|---------|--------|
| Functionality | **30%** |
| UI/UX | **20%** |
| Innovation | **20%** |
| Security | **15%** |
| Ecosystem Impact | **15%** |

Ends with final submission & live demo day.

---

## Phase 4 ‚Äî Evaluation & Ecosystem Transition  
**Late March 2026**

Includes:

- Livestreamed awards ceremony  
- Judge evaluations  
- Post-event surveys  
- Transition of hackathon portal into a **permanent bounty developer hub**  
- Top projects invited into grants/accelerators  

